*SHOOTER INSTRUCTIONS*

OPERATOR CONTROLS (Non-Driver Gamepad)

Right Trigger : Spin shooter flywheel (0% to 100% based on squeeze)

Y Button      : Spin shooter at 100% MAX power

Right Bumper  : Run intake forward (pull in / feed element)

Left Bumper   : Run intake backward (outtake / clear jam)

HOW TO SHOOT IN A MATCH

Step 1: Press and hold Right Trigger (or Y Button) to spin up flywheel.
Step 2: Wait 1 to 2 seconds for the wheel to reach full speed.
Step 3: Press and hold Right Bumper to feed element into the flywheel.
Step 4: Release all buttons when done.

____________________________________________________________________

*TELLYOP_AUTO INSTRUCTIONS*

WHAT THE ROBOT DOES IN AUTONOMOUS

Step 1: Drives FORWARD for 1.0 second.
Step 2: Turns LEFT for 1.0 second.
Step 3: STOPS all drive motors.
Step 4: Starts SHOOTER flywheel at 100% power and waits 1.5 seconds to spin up.
Step 5: Runs INTAKE forward for 1.0 second to feed element into shooter.
Step 6: STOPS all shooter and intake motors.

MATCH START PROCEDURE

Step 1: On Driver Station app, select "Basic Telly Auto" from Autonomous side.
Step 2: Load game element into the intake/feeder mechanism.
Step 3: Press INIT on Driver Station phone.
Step 4: Align robot on field starting position.
Step 5: When match begins, press START (Play button). Hands off controllers!

