*TELLYOP_HANDOFF INSTRUCTIONS*

CONTROLLER ROLE BREAKDOWN

Active Driver  : Controls drivetrain (strafing, moving, turning).

Operator       : Controls shooter and intake mechanism.

Whoever is NOT driving automatically becomes the Operator!

DRIVER CONTROLS (Active Driver)

Left Stick Y  : Drive Forward / Backward

Left Stick X  : Strafe Left / Right

Right Stick X : Turn Left / Right

Button A      : Claim driver control (transfer driving to your controller)

OPERATOR CONTROLS (Non-Driver)

Right Bumper  : Spin intake IN (pull element in)

Left Bumper   : Spin intake OUT (reverse / eject element)

Right Trigger : Spin shooter flywheel (0% to 100% variable speed)

Y Button      : Spin shooter flywheel at 100% MAX power

HOW HANDOFF WORKS IN A MATCH

Start of match : Gamepad 1 is default Driver; Gamepad 2 is default Operator.

Swapping roles : Press Button A on either controller to take over driving.

Rumble feedback: Controller taking over driving will rumble for 0.5s.
Controller losing driver control will rumble 2 quick blips.

